  "prompt": "Will it be fine if both husband and wife having same blood group?",
  "response": "Yes, it is generally fine for both husband and wife to have the same blood group. Blood type compatibility is more important when it comes to pregnancy, as certain combinations can pose risks such as Rh incompatibility if the mother is Rh-negative and the baby is Rh-positive. However, having the same blood group does not inherently pose any health issues for the couple. \n\nIn terms of blood donation, having the same blood type can be advantageous for them, as they can easily donate to each other if needed. Always consulting with a healthcare provider for personalized medical advice is recommended when considering any implications related to blood types, especially in the context of pregnancy or planning a family.",
